citations:
    citation-agot-jon-viii:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Jon VIII"
            text_from_source: "He saw arm and hand on the floor, black fingers wriggling in a pool of moonlight … 'Burn!' the raven cawed. 'Burn, burn, burn!' … Jon plunged his hand into the flames, grabbed a fistful of the burning drapes, and whipped them at the dead man."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "The bodies of Othor and Jafer Flowers (two of Benjen Stark's rangers) are found beyond the Wall with blue eyes and black hands — signs of the Others. Sam deduces they have not rotted as a fresh corpse should. The bodies are brought back to Castle Black. That night, Othor rises as a wight and attacks Lord Commander Mormont in his solar. Jon Snow kills it with fire, burning his right hand badly. Ser Jaremy Rykker and four others are slain by the second wight (Jafer Flowers). Jon learns of Ned Stark's imprisonment. Lord Mormont reveals he knew Jon as a man grown would have to choose between his oath and his family."
